CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, February 12, 1966, pg. 1B reads: "Kappa Silhouettes - Members of the socially prominent Kappa Silhouettes celebrated their 16th anniversary recently by entertaining several hundred guests at a gay Black and White Ball. The affair was held in the beautiful ballroom of the Hotel Penn Sheraton.  The organization  is composed of wives of members of Kappa Alpha Psi Fraternity and is headed by Mrs. James (Ethel) Stewart (Seated center) as president."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of twenty Kappa Alpha Psi Silhouette members, including Ethel Stewart seated in center, posed in Penn Sheraton Hotel for Black and White Ball, another version
